    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It's not, it's still your assembly block. Commenting out `b := m` also makes the test pass. The error is that you are assigning to a variable with type `bytes`, but the layout in memory for this type is `[len, item a, item b, ...]`, and since you are just setting a single slot in memory, it reads the result of your `xor` as the length of the `bytes` type. This works:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.10;\r\n\r\nimport \"forge-std/Test.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract AssemblyTest is Test {\r\n  address public constant SOME_CONTRACT_ADDR = 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000002001;\r\n\r\n  function setUp() public {}\r\n\r\n  function testAssembly() public {\r\n    address deployAddr = deployCode(\"MyContract.sol\");\r\n    vm.etch(SOME_CONTRACT_ADDR, deployAddr.code);\r\n\r\n    address addr = address(this);\r\n    bytes memory b;\r\n    assembly {\r\n      // Retrieve memory pointer, assign to `b`\r\n      b := mload(0x40)\r\n      // Store the size in memory of `b` (32 bytes)\r\n      mstore(b, 0x20)\r\n      // Store value\r\n      mstore(add(b, 0x20), xor(0x140000000000000000000000000000000000000000, addr))\r\n      // Increase free memory pointer\r\n      mstore(0x40, add(b, 0x40))\r\n    }\r\n    emit log_bytes(b);\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```",
